    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1965-08-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1965-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="168"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                <head>168. National Security Action Memorandum No. 337<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d168fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National Security File, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>s, <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss>
                        337. Top Secret; COMINT. Prepared by <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">McGeorge
                            Bundy</persName>. A copy was sent to the Director of the Budget.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1965-08-10">August 10, 1965</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>MEMORANDUM TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Director of Central Intelligence</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>US Intelligence Facilities in Pakistan</item>
                </list>
                <p>In the light of your responses to my memorandum of July 6 on this subject, the
                    President approves your unanimous recommendation <pb facs="0372" n="334"
                        xml:id="pg_334"/> that we proceed as a matter of urgency to develop
                    alternate facilities, and requests a firm recommendation on this matter as soon
                    as feasible.<note n="2" xml:id="d168fn2">On August 21 the Department asked the
                        Embassy in [<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>] to comment [<hi
                            rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]. (Telegram [<hi rend="italic"
                            >text not declassified</hi>] to [<hi rend="italic">text not
                            declassified</hi>]; Department of State, <gloss target="#t_INR1"
                            >INR</gloss>/IL Historical Files, [<hi rend="italic">text not
                            declassified</hi>] Cables, [<hi rend="italic">text not
                        declassified</hi>]) On August 25 the Department requested a similar
                        assessment from the Embassy in Tehran; see <ref target="frus1964-68v22#d94">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1964–1968, vol. XXII, Document
                            94</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>He also approves the Secretary of State’s recommendation that no further
                    additions or improvements to the facilities be undertaken at this time.</p>
                <p>Finally, he asks that the agencies concerned keep this matter under continuous
                    review and prepare, on a contingency basis, a list of measures they would
                    recommend if it were decided to use this means of convincing Pakistan of our
                    dissatisfaction with its current posture.<note n="3" xml:id="d168fn3">The
                        Department transmitted the conclusions of <gloss target="#t_NSAM1"
                            >NSAM</gloss> No. 337 to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MCWPJ1"
                            >McConaughy</persName> on August 19. (Telegram 28 to Rawalpindi;
                        Department of State, <gloss target="#t_INR1">INR</gloss>/IL Historical
                        Files, [<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>] Cables,
                        Rawalpindi)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
